00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:22.809
One of the things that Muhammad Ali was so
great at was he was tall and Iím going to

00:06:22.809 --> 00:06:32.119
have Brian throw a jab and he would ñ Muhammad
Ali would just kind of rock back.

00:06:32.119 --> 00:06:37.729
As he would move his punch, he would rock
away from the punch and have the ability to

00:06:37.729 --> 00:06:39.699
come right back and throw something.

00:06:39.699 --> 00:06:42.849
If he throws a right hand, I can rock back.

00:06:42.849 --> 00:06:44.759
But if I rock back, now watch.

00:06:44.759 --> 00:06:48.509
Heís going to throw a right hand and Iím
going to rock back and not roll my shoulder

00:06:48.509 --> 00:06:51.330
and he will hit me with that right hand.

00:06:51.330 --> 00:06:52.539
See?

00:06:52.539 --> 00:06:58.020
Now what I want to do when I rock back, I
want to roll that shoulder so that Iím protecting

00:06:58.020 --> 00:07:01.409
myself from that there.

00:07:01.409 --> 00:07:08.089
So I can rock back from the jab, the right
hand, either one, and it puts you in the position.

00:07:08.089 --> 00:07:13.619
You rock back and when you rock back ñ Diamond
Jim MacDonald, a fighter that I used to work

00:07:13.619 --> 00:07:17.279
with who fought Michael Spinks for the light
heavyweight championship of the world was

00:07:17.279 --> 00:07:19.169
fantastic at this.

00:07:19.169 --> 00:07:20.679
He would stick his jab.

00:07:20.679 --> 00:07:21.839
He would rock back, boom!

00:07:21.839 --> 00:07:23.870
Come on the top of the right hand.

00:07:23.870 --> 00:07:29.240
He knocked out a bunch of fighters with that
and had Michael Spinks hurt in the world championship

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:32.199
fight just by rocking back and throwing that
right hand.

